[0.0,"o","⠟⠋⠁\u001b[39m           \u001b[0m\r\r\n                                                                                \u001b[0m\r\r\n      \u001b[0mWelcome to the new Kiro CLI UX! Use \u001b[0m\u001b[38;2;193;154;255m/feedback\u001b[39m\u001b[0m to share your thoughts.\u001b[0m     \u001b[0m\r\r\n        \u001b[0mPrefer the classic experience? Relaunch with \u001b[0m\u001b[38;2;193;154;255mkiro-cli --classic\u001b[39m\u001b[0m.\u001b[0m        \u001b[0m\r\r\n\u001b[38;2;38;38;38m────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[39m\u001b[0m\r\r\n\u001b[38;2;0;215;135m●\u001b[39m \u001b[0mTransform any idea into fully working code. What do you want to build today?\u001b[0m  \u001b[0m\r\r\n\u001b[38;2;38;38;38m────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[39m\u001b[0"]
[0.0,"o","m\r\r\n  \u001b[48;2;38;38;38m\u001b[0m\u001b[48;2;38;38;38mBuild a Rust CLI tool called crabbymark that renders a markdown file to       \u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\r\n  \u001b[48;2;38;38;38mGitHub-styled HTML with syntax highlighting and opens it in the default       \u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\r\n  \u001b[48;2;38;38;38mbrowser. Use clap (derive) for CLI parsing, pulldown-cmark for markdown       \u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\r\n  \u001b[48;2;38;38;38mparsing (with tables, strikethrough, tasklists, footnotes), and syntect for   \u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\r\n  \u001b[48;2;38;38;38msyntax highlighting by intercepting code block events and re-injecting        \u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\r\n  \u001b[48;2;38;38;38mhighlighted HTML. Use InspiredGitHub theme for light (default) and            \u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\r\n  \u001b[48;2;38;38;38mbase16-ocean.dark for dark (--dark flag). All CSS should be inline/embedded in\u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\r\n  \u001b[48;2;38;38;38mthe HTML using GitHub's color palettes. With --pdf, use headless_chrome (with \u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\r\n  \u001b[48;2;38;38;38mfetch feature) to generate a PDF via print_to_pdf() in the same directory as  \u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\r\n  \u001b[48;2;38;38;38mthe input file. Use"]
[0.0,"o"," the open crate for browser opening (fall back to printing \u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\r\n  \u001b[48;2;38;38;38mthe file path on headless systems), tempfile for temp files, and anyhow for   \u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\r\n  \u001b[48;2;38;38;38merrors. Include --version and --help support, a README with usage examples and\u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\r\n  \u001b[48;2;38;38;38ma note about Chrome/Chromium being needed for PDF, and a .gitignore covering  \u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\r\n  \u001b[48;2;38;38;38m/target, *.pdf, and *.html.\u001b[0m\u001b[48;2;38;38;38m                                                   \u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\r\n                                                                                \u001b[0m\r\r\n  \u001b[0mLet me understand what you're asking for: You want a Rust CLI tool called     \u001b[0m\r\r\n  \u001b[0m\u001b[38;2;0;135;255mcrabbymark\u001b[39m\u001b[0m that converts Markdown files to GitHub-styled HTML with syntax     \u001b[0m\r\r\n  highlighting, can open the result in a browser, and optionally export to PDF  \u001b[0m\r\r\n  via headless Chrome.\u001b[0m                                                          \u001b[0m\r\r\n  \u001b[0m\u001b[0m                       "]
[0.0,"o","                                                       \u001b[0m\r\r\n  \u001b[0mBefore I create the implementation plan, let me explore the current workspace \u001b[0m\r\r\n  and do some research.\u001b[0m                                                         \u001b[0m\r\r\n\u001b[38;2;0;215;135m●\u001b[39m \u001b[0mLs\u001b[0m\u001b[38;2;0;135;255m .\u001b[39m                                                                          \u001b[0m\r\r\n\u001b[38;2;0;215;135m●\u001b[39m \u001b[0mWebSearch\u001b[0m\u001b[38;2;0;135;255m \"pulldown-cmark rust code block events CodeBlockKind syntax         \u001b[0m\r\r\n  \u001b[38;2;0;135;255mhighlighting intercept\"\u001b[39m                                                       \u001b[0m\r\r\n\u001b[38;2;0;215;135m●\u001b[39m \u001b[0mWebFetch\u001b[0m\u001b[38;2;0;135;255m \u001b]8;;https://bandarra.me/posts/Rust-Markdown-Syntax-Highlighting-A-Practical-Guide\u0007bandarra.me/posts/Rust-Markdown-Syntax-Highlighting-A-Pra...\u001b]8;;\u0007\u001b[39m         \u001b[0m\r\r\n    \u001b[38;2;98;98;98m╰ \u001b[39m\u001b[38;2;98;98;98msearch_terms=CodeBlockKind Event intercept syntect highlighted HTML\u001b[39m       \u001b[0m\r\r\n  \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m14.8k chars\u001b"]
